---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="ZT1 Prep's privacy policy. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your information."
>
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-stone lg:prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p class="lead text-xl text-stone-600">
        Your privacy matters. This policy explains what information we collect and how we use it.
      </p>

      <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> January 2025</p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>Information You Provide</h3>

      <p>
        We collect information you voluntarily provide, including:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact information</strong> — If you email us, we receive your email address and message content</li>
        <li><strong>Newsletter subscription</strong> — If you subscribe, we collect your email address</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Automatically Collected Information</h3>

      <p>
        When you visit our site, we automatically collect:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Usage data</strong> — Pages visited, time spent, referring sites, and general navigation patterns</li>
        <li><strong>Device information</strong> — Browser type, operating system, and device type</li>
        <li><strong>IP address</strong> — Used for general location (country/region) and security purposes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use Information</h2>

      <p>
        We use collected information to:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Improve our content and user experience</li>
        <li>Respond to your inquiries</li>
        <li>Send newsletters (if subscribed)</li>
        <li>Analyze site traffic and usage patterns</li>
        <li>Prevent fraud and maintain security</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information to third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and Tracking</h2>

      <h3>What Are Cookies?</h3>

      <p>
        Cookies are small text files stored on your device that help websites function and gather usage information.
      </p>

      <h3>Cookies We Use</h3>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Essential cookies</strong> — Required for basic site functionality</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> — Help us understand how visitors use the site (e.g., Google Analytics)</li>
        <li><strong>Affiliate cookies</strong> — Track affiliate link clicks for commission purposes</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Managing Cookies</h3>

      <p>
        You can control cookies through your browser settings. Note that disabling certain cookies may affect site functionality.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>

      <p>
        We use third-party services that may collect information:
      </p>

      <h3>Analytics</h3>

      <p>
        We use Google Analytics to understand site usage. Google Analytics collects anonymous data about your visit. You can opt out using the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>Affiliate Networks</h3>

      <p>
        When you click affiliate links, our affiliate partners (including Amazon) may place cookies on your device. These cookies track your purchase for commission purposes. See our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a> for more information.
      </p>

      <h3>Hosting</h3>

      <p>
        Our site is hosted by third-party providers who may collect standard server logs including IP addresses, access times, and pages requested.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Security</h2>

      <p>
        We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information. However, no internet transmission is completely secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security of data transmitted to our site.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>

      <p>
        Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal information:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> — Request a copy of information we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Correction</strong> — Request correction of inaccurate information</li>
        <li><strong>Deletion</strong> — Request deletion of your information</li>
        <li><strong>Opt-out</strong> — Unsubscribe from marketing communications</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        To exercise these rights, <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>

      <p>
        Our site is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13. If you believe we have collected such information, please <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>External Links</h2>

      <p>
        Our site contains links to external websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of other sites. We encourage you to review privacy policies of sites you visit.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>

      <p>
        We may update this policy periodically. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>

      <p>
        Questions about this privacy policy? <a href="/contact">Contact us</a>.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm">
        Last updated: January 2025
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
